org.eclipse.viatra.dse.objectives.impl

Class BaseObjective

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.viatra.dse.objectives.impl.BaseObjective
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IObjective
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CompositeObjective, ConstraintsObjective, DummyHardObjective, MinimalDepthHardObjective, NoRuleActivationsHardObjective, TrajectoryCostSoftObjective

    public abstract class BaseObjective
extends java.lang.Object
implements IObjective
    This abstract class implements the basic functionality of an objective (IObjective namely its name, comparator, level and fitness hard constraint.

                                        java.util.Comparator<java.lang.Double> fitnessConstraintComparator)
        Adds a hard constraint on the fitness value. For example, the fitness value must be better than 10 to accept the current state as a solution.
        Parameters:

        fitnessConstraintComparator - Comparator to determine if the current state is better than the given value.
